FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1773857158
OL,3,CHotter than holiday hotspots: UK
OL,4,Cspring surge sees temperatures soar
OL,6,FThe position of that area of high
OL,7,Fpressure is also creating a warm
OL,8,Fsoutheasterly airflow which will drag
OL,9,Fin warm air from the near continent,
OL,10,Ffurther encouraging a rise in
OL,11,Ftemperatures.
OL,13,FThe warmest areas are those that will
OL,14,Fget the benefit of the warm air and
OL,15,Flovely sunshine but be sheltered from
OL,16,Fthe cooling effect of the breeze which
OL,17,Fwill peg temperatures back a little
OL,18,Facross more coastal parts of the
OL,19,Fsoutheast.
OL,21,FHow unusual is this?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
